:::info
Snapshots are backups of the database directory of a polkadot or kusama node. If you start a node it will start building from start (genesis), which will take a while. If you download an up to date database your node will be running quicker.

The snapshots are in paritydb format `--database paritydb` and pruned `--pruning 1000`, which is sufficient for a validator node.
:::

## Kusama paritydb snapshot

### Download the database
Download for later extraction.
```bash
wget http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/paritydb-ksm.lz4
```

### Install the database directly
Install to `/home/polkadot/.local/share/polkadot/chains/ksmcc3` or change to your target directory.
```bash
curl -o - -L http://snapshot.stakeworld.nl/paritydb-ksm.lz4 | lz4 -c -d - | tar -x -C /home/polkadot/.local/share/polkadot/chains/ksmcc3
```

